cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on performance modeling of a distributed computing framework (Hadoop MapReduce).
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper describes the dataflow and cost information within the map and reduce tasks of a job execution.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses finding optimal configuration settings for running MapReduce jobs.
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper deals with large-scale data analytics.
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper focuses on performance modeling of a computing framework.
